# NourishNet MVP — Client Scope

**Tagline:** "Nourishing communities, together."

**Flow:** Providers + Recipients only (no other roles in core MVP).

---

## Core Flow

1. **Provider posts surplus** — quantity, pickup address, pickup window, categories, allergens
2. **Recipients receive push notification** — based on city/radius + preferences
3. **Recipient requests/claims** — either instant claim OR 2–5 minute request window (recommended for fairness)
4. **Recipient picks up** — at provider location, within time window
5. **Verification at pickup** — simplest: PIN shown by provider (recipient enters in app); OR "I picked up" + optional photo (less secure)
6. **Impact is logged** — meals rescued + optional appreciation note (anonymous)

---

## Must-Have Features

### Provider
- Auth (phone/email)
- Create listing in <60 seconds
- Manage listings (edit/cancel/expire)
- View "picked up / not picked up"
- Basic reports (count + simple weekly email)

### Recipient
- Auth (phone OTP)
- Notification settings (city/radius/categories/quiet hours)
- Listings feed + map
- Claim/request flow
- Pickup verification (PIN)
- My history + impact
- Optional appreciation notes

### Admin
- Provider verification (basic)
- Disputes/reports
- Basic analytics dashboard

---

## Fairness

- **Daily/weekly caps** — e.g., 1/day, 3/week
- **Request window + fair selection** for high-demand posts
- **Cooldown for no-shows** — claim but don't pick up
- **"Need food today" toggle (Demand Pulse)** — used as a weight, not a gate

---

## Feature Set (Reference)

- **Food Listing:** Food type (prepared, produce, baked goods), quantity (meals/boxes), pickup window countdown, location auto-filled
- **Smart Alerts:** "Food available within 1 mile", "Pickup closing in 20 minutes", priority alerts for high-need users
- **Claim & Pickup:** One-tap claim, navigation link, QR code or pickup PIN, photo confirmation
- **Trust & Safety:** Basic ratings (no public shaming), food safety guidelines, flag/report flow, repeat trusted partners
- **Impact Tracking:** Meals saved, pounds rescued, CO₂ equivalent, streaks & badges

---

## Required Fair Use Policy

Include: claim limits, no resale of food, no account farming, no discrimination or harassment, consequences for no-shows.

**Enforcement:** Cooldowns, temporary suspensions, admin review queue, device/phone number safeguards.

---

## Enhanced Alerts

- Priority alerts for users marked "high need"
- Quiet hours
- Category-based alerts (prepared meals, produce, baby food, halal/vegan, etc.)
- Predictive: "This bakery usually posts at 8:30pm — stay ready"

---

## AI-Assisted Matching (Fairness)

- Match food type → recipient needs; distance → fastest pickup; quantity → household size

---

## Micro-Communities & Neighborhood Circles

- Apartment complex, church/mosque/temple, college campus, parent groups, senior support circles
- Share internal food alerts, assign trusted volunteers, coordinate pickups, quiet accountability

---

## For Restaurants & Stores

- One-tap repost from yesterday's listing, auto-suggest quantities, "Closing soon?" quick post, donation summaries, printable/downloadable tax receipts

---

## Impact Dashboard

- Meals rescued, families helped, food waste prevented, CO₂ equivalent, personal timeline, community milestones
- Shareable cards: "Our block rescued 312 meals this month."

---

## Demand Pulse

- "I need food today" toggle — expires end of day (local), optional and anonymous by default, feeds city/circle demand counter, helps routing + donor awareness

---

## Private Impact Notes

- After completed pickup: one-tap optional "Would you like to send a note of appreciation?"
- Quick taps or short message (max 240 chars), anonymous by default
- Visible to: donor organization, admin dashboards — not public

---

## Basic Business Identity (Paid Tier)

- Business/org name, type (Restaurant/Bakery/Café, Grocery, Church, School, Community Org/Pantry), primary contact name, email, OTP-verified phone
- **Location & Pickup:** Address, city, state, ZIP, pickup instructions, typical days/times, parking notes
- **Food Safety:** Required checkbox acknowledging local food safety guidelines
- **Posting Preferences:** Surplus categories, allergens, most common posting time, "Usually perishable?" toggle
- **Impact & Visibility:** Monthly impact summary?, anonymous appreciation notes?, report format (email PDF / in-app)
- **Billing (Paid):** Card, billing email, monthly/annual, tax-exempt checkbox
- **Staff Access:** Invite staff emails, roles (poster/admin); after onboarding: "Verified Partner" badge, volume-based trust score

**One-line during registration:** "We only ask for what's needed to coordinate safe, reliable food pickups."

---

## Privacy & Data (CRITICAL)

- Comply with GDPR (EU), CCPA/CPRA (California), and general privacy laws
- Required: Privacy Policy, Data Retention Policy, user consent for location, notifications, optional photos

---

## Mobile vs Web/Admin

- **Mobile:** Provider post flow, recipient feed + claim, verification entry, settings + impact
- **Web/Admin:** Provider approvals, reports queue, dashboard stats

---

When implementing or discussing features, align with this scope. Prioritize MVP (Providers + Recipients, core flow, fairness, PIN verification, impact logging) and reference the full feature set for consistency.
